Since $\cos{Y}=\frac{7}{25}$, we have $\cos{Y}=\frac{YZ}{XY}=\frac{YZ}{25}=\frac{7}{25}$.  From this, we can see that $YZ=25\cdot\frac{7}{25}=7$.  Then, from the Pythagorean Theorem, $XZ=\sqrt{XY^2-YZ^2}=\sqrt{25^2-7^2}=\sqrt{576}=24$.  Finally, we have $\tan{X}=\frac{YZ}{XZ}=\boxed{\frac{7}{24}}$.

